Note: ============================================================================
Note: BIT-CAST HELPERS
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "float_to_bits_oklab" takes x as Float returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Bit-cast Float64 to its 64-bit integer pattern.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Inline assembly reads the float-occupying stack slot as integer.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Single mov.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Constant-time.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        mov rax, qword ptr [rbp-8]
        mov qword ptr [rbp-16], rax
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Process called "store_float_at_oklab" takes ptr as Integer, offset as Integer, value as Float returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Bit-cast a Float64 and store at ptr + offset.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    float_to_bits_oklab + memory_set_int64.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Two movs + one store.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller owns ptr.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let bits be float_to_bits_oklab(value)
    Let _w be Memory.memory_set_int64(ptr, offset, bits)
    Return 0
End Process
